151
00:11:45,525 --> 00:11:47,325
It wasn't because you didn't like him.

152
00:11:47,325 --> 00:11:51,835
You had a reason to do that, and he should know, too.

153
00:11:51,835 --> 00:11:54,845
You're so unbelievable, Grandma.

154
00:11:54,845 --> 00:11:59,885
By the way, I think he changed a bit.

155
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,135
What do you mean by that?

156
00:12:02,135 --> 00:12:08,075
I thought he'd be so happy if I told him you paid the money back

157
00:12:08,075 --> 00:12:10,445
and freed yourself from that bastard.

158
00:12:10,445 --> 00:12:16,655
But he was only a tiny bit happy.

159
00:12:16,655 --> 00:12:23,075
I think he was very hurt by you.

160
00:12:23,955 --> 00:12:28,505
That's why... you shouldn't have told him that.

161
00:12:28,505 --> 00:12:31,315
Nothing is going on between us anymore.

162
00:12:31,315 --> 00:12:35,575
You dated that bastard even though you secretly liked the Director.

163
00:12:35,575 --> 00:12:38,905
How could I do nothing while knowing that?

164
00:12:38,905 --> 00:12:41,175
I had to correct things.

165
00:12:41,925 --> 00:12:43,630
Ji Yeong,

166
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:50,060
it's not too late to be good to Director.

167
00:12:50,065 --> 00:12:55,685
Looks like he still has some feelings for you, too.

168
00:12:55,685 --> 00:12:59,195
He's just a little upset. Okay?

169
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:05,865
So, you'd better hang onto him before another girl takes him away.

170
00:13:05,865 --> 00:13:09,005
Ease his disappointment little by little.

171
00:13:10,275 --> 00:13:12,725
No, Grandma.

172
00:13:12,725 --> 00:13:15,935
I don't have the right to like him.

173
00:13:16,525 --> 00:13:18,455
Aigoo...

174
00:13:18,455 --> 00:13:20,865
My goodness...

175
00:13:20,865 --> 00:13:22,490
Yes.

176
00:13:23,045 --> 00:13:29,375
Even I think you did the wrong thing.

177
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:34,675
I know it was because of the money, but you were with someone else.

178
00:13:37,155 --> 00:13:39,310
But still, Ji Yeong...

179
00:13:40,385 --> 00:13:45,275
reflect on what you did and be better from now on.

180
00:13:45,275 --> 00:13:49,505
I'm sure he'll feel better, too.

181
00:13:50,695 --> 00:13:52,490
Grandma...

182
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:58,345
I have no right. I can't do that to him.

183
00:13:58,345 --> 00:14:01,705
He needs to find someone nice instead of me.

184
00:14:02,545 --> 00:14:07,085
So don't tell me stuff like that anymore.

185
00:14:07,085 --> 00:14:10,465
J-Ji Yeong. Ji Yeong...

186
00:14:11,665 --> 00:14:16,315
Aigoo, I feel so sorry for her.

187
00:14:33,955 --> 00:14:38,705
 For lending money to that meanie stepmother, 

188
00:14:38,705 --> 00:14:43,835
 he demanded to date Ji Yeong, apparently. 

189
00:14:43,835 --> 00:14:51,855
 That's why my sweet Ji Yeong was forced to date that scoundrel. 

190
00:14:59,695 --> 00:15:01,895
And I had no idea.

191
00:15:35,285 --> 00:15:37,315
What's with that guy?

192
00:15:40,465 --> 00:15:42,415
Excuse me, Ahjussi.

193
00:15:42,415 --> 00:15:46,235
Come out. Come out.

194
00:15:46,235 --> 00:15:49,465
Ahjussi, Ahjussi, come here.

195
00:15:55,905 --> 00:15:58,435
You're that ahjussi, aren't you?

196
00:15:58,435 --> 00:16:01,355
 J-Jin Dan. 

197
00:16:02,235 --> 00:16:05,475
Seriously. What's with you?

198
00:16:05,475 --> 00:16:07,665
What are you doing here?

199
00:16:07,665 --> 00:16:09,015
Why are you here?

200
00:16:09,015 --> 00:16:12,625
I was looking for a place nearby.

201
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:16,155
I wasn't sure if it was this way or that way.

202
00:16:16,155 --> 00:16:18,675
Why did you hide when you ran into me, then?

203
00:16:18,675 --> 00:16:20,565
What? I didn't hide.

204
00:16:20,565 --> 00:16:25,505
I was going to go that way, but I came because you called me.

205
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:29,975
I'm sorry if it looked that way.

206
00:16:31,175 --> 00:16:36,105
Stay away from this place if you don't want to be mistaken again.

207
00:16:36,105 --> 00:16:39,365
I won't forgive you if I catch you doing this again.

208
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:41,685
I'll call the police.

209
00:16:41,685 --> 00:16:45,830
There are CCTVs everywhere here. Okay?

210
00:16:46,345 --> 00:16:48,055
Aren't you going to answer?

211
00:16:48,055 --> 00:16:50,375
O-Okay.

212
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:54,845
Seriously. Everything is annoying me this morning.

213
00:17:04,655 --> 00:17:06,455
Leave!

214
00:17:10,925 --> 00:17:12,665
Aren't you leaving?

215
00:17:23,245 --> 00:17:28,015
Mom, why was that insurance man lurking around our house?

216
00:17:28,015 --> 00:17:30,725
What? Who?

217
00:17:30,725 --> 00:17:32,885
What's your relationship with him?

218
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:35,765
W-What do you mean? Nothing is going on.

219
00:17:35,765 --> 00:17:40,275
Why was he peeping at me in front of our house?

220
00:17:40,275 --> 00:17:41,505
Are you sure nothing is going on?

221
00:17:41,505 --> 00:17:42,865
I'm telling you.

222
00:17:42,865 --> 00:17:45,035
 Mom, you'd better not see him from now on. 

223
00:17:45,035 --> 00:17:46,935
Don't sign up for his insurance, either.

224
00:17:46,935 --> 00:17:50,385
He really bothers me, okay?

225
00:17:50,385 --> 00:17:51,685
Okay, I won't.

226
00:17:51,685 --> 00:17:56,365
But he travels a lot because he sells insurance.

227
00:17:56,365 --> 00:17:58,625
That's how he probably ended up at our house.

228
00:17:58,625 --> 00:18:00,505
So don't worry about him.

229
00:18:00,505 --> 00:18:02,975
Okay, bye.

230
00:18:11,365 --> 00:18:14,505
Sang Gu, are you crazy? Are you out of your mind?

231
00:18:14,505 --> 00:18:16,735
Why were you lurking in front of our house?

232
00:18:16,735 --> 00:18:19,375
Are you determined to ruin Jin Dan's life?

233
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:20,915
Why are you doing this?

234
00:18:20,915 --> 00:18:24,885
Ae Gyo, why did you raise him as such a brat?

235
00:18:24,885 --> 00:18:28,865
I'm old enough to be his father, but he treated me so rudely.

236
00:18:28,865 --> 00:18:30,645
I was really upset.

237
00:18:30,645 --> 00:18:33,095
I'm still his father.

238
00:18:33,095 --> 00:18:35,565
Someone might hear you. Are you crazy?

239
00:18:35,565 --> 00:18:38,175
It wasn't just anyone.

240
00:18:39,435 --> 00:18:43,235
I was treated like that by my son. It makes me so upset.

241
00:18:43,235 --> 00:18:48,825
Sang Gu, he's been upset since his adoption got canceled recently.

242
00:18:48,825 --> 00:18:52,615
You can't expect him to treat you nicely when you get caught acting weird.

243
00:18:52,615 --> 00:18:54,695
His adoption was canceled? Why?

244
00:18:54,695 --> 00:18:56,535
I don't know.

245
00:18:57,145 --> 00:18:59,145
You don't have to know all that.

246
00:18:59,145 --> 00:19:02,555
Anyway, don't go anywhere near Jin Dan anymore.

247
00:19:02,555 --> 00:19:04,295
His adoption was canceled.

248
00:19:04,295 --> 00:19:07,295
What if Chairman Gong found out you were his birth father?

249
00:19:07,295 --> 00:19:09,825
We'd be done for.

250
00:19:09,825 --> 00:19:12,475
Okay. I'll be careful not to get caught from now on.

251
00:19:12,475 --> 00:19:15,325
Are you saying you'd keep peeping at Jin Dan?

252
00:19:15,325 --> 00:19:18,275
How could I not see my son?

253
00:19:18,275 --> 00:19:22,235
Hearing he's my son, I can't stop thinking about him.

254
00:19:22,235 --> 00:19:24,275
I miss him, and I want to hug him.

255
00:19:24,275 --> 00:19:26,360
What are you saying?

256
00:19:26,825 --> 00:19:28,195
You must've lost your mind.

257
00:19:28,195 --> 00:19:31,365
Sang Gu, get it together!

258
00:19:35,935 --> 00:19:40,055
I came to apologize for everything that has been going on.

259
00:19:52,385 --> 00:19:57,255
Both of our families went through a lot recently.

260
00:19:58,335 --> 00:20:01,045
Because I felt betrayed by my wife,

261
00:20:01,045 --> 00:20:05,545
I gave the innocent Pil Sung a hard time.

262
00:20:05,545 --> 00:20:07,060
And...

263
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:12,690
I even gave you a hard time, President Go and Seon Yeong.

